    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix hashtable_destroy crash when freefunc is NULL\n\n### Summary\nThe hashtable_destroy function in the common utilities module was causing segmentation faults when attempting to destroy hash tables under certain edge conditions. The crash occurred because the function attempted to call the freefunc function pointer without first verifying it was not NULL.\n\nThis issue was observed when the hashtable was created with a custom free function that somehow became NULL during the lifetime of the table, or when memory corruption affected the hashtable structure. The crash manifested as a segfault in hashtable_destroy when it tried to free node data.\n\nThe root cause was missing defensive checks before calling the freefunc pointer. This fix adds proper NULL checks for the freefunc before invoking it in hashtable_destroy and related functions.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/hashtable/hashtable.c`: Added NULL checks for freefunc before calling it in hashtable_destroy, hashtable_insert, and hashtable_remove functions.\n"
}